Current mainstream operating systems (Windows,Linux,BSD,...) have
become very heavy and complex with time, and are getting heavier and
more complex with every new release. Programs are following the same
trend, so much so that a computer from ten years ago cannot even run
them properly, even those that existed ten years ago.

Omega is my personal attempt at finding out why. I figure, by writing
an operating system I might really understand what programs do today
that they didn't yesterday and why.

